README.md and SKILL.md must stay in sync with mycelium.sh.

README is for humans discovering the repo. SKILL.md is for agents
loading the convention. Both must reflect the current commands,
patterns, and capabilities. When you add a command, update both.
When you change behavior, update both.

Story: we added follow, refs, kinds, and branch commands during a
single session. SKILL.md was updated with the three patterns
(accumulation, multi-edge, planning graph) and the 'On arrival'
section. But the README didn't exist yet — it was written after
the commands, not alongside them. That worked this time because
it was a first draft. Going forward, command changes and doc
changes should be in the same commit.
